<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://tim3newman.users.btopenworld.com/taziir/News/DDR.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 5:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> meh!</span><hr size=1> pets in plane of water is absolutely banned. I'm an ornery and cranky wizard who &lt;3s the xuzl, but never should it screw with positioning. If it touches a wall in water with its suck positioning, tank flies off to zone in, which is a remarkably moronic trait for a zone to have. as wall pinned mobs go, the xuzl aa etc can go into the side of the mob, and cause no problems if the pin holds. corner pinned mobs can take it np to the ass from them. often times someone with stupid use of a pet or pet aa can stick it to a wall pinned mob and break the pin, sending it into the death-corner. the pets also crowd melees, and if on a wall will interrupt tank movement. people who use the aa should be smart about it, and use their brains. in situations where a mob needs to be pushed, I'll use the aa especially.<br>
<br>
on trivial stuff I recall using the dpschannel synchronized 'canada attack', where a phenomenal amount of swarm pets are used to fling a mob across the zone. I remember when tvk in vex thal some time ago had a mob gate by him- assuredly the only time something like that happened- which sent him to us all the way across the room. Naturally I announced that this mob needed to be sent straight to canada, and the fury of 3 maxed mage aa pets and 7 wizard xuzl maxed aas(59 pets?) were shot at him. I can say that the mob went flying FAST with all of that behind him.<br>
<br>
this AA has strange behavior, especially with charmed mobs. it was reported to me that a wizard used the CoX aa against a giant that was being charm fought against, which immediately turned on the druid splatting him. once I was in bot duoing with a mage when I decided it would be fun(wiz can heal pets, too~sorta...). i used the call of xuzl aa against a mob, which started summon rune reverse kite action, that was most bad. nonetheless, it died, not me. <br>
<br>
by now, I use the cox aa as a form of positioning, not dps. the spell is a little bit of dps, don't let it interfere with anything. 11dps is not a lot for the troubles it may cause.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1>General EQ Discussion</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href="www.graffe.com">Home</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
